=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Looking at the mapped reaction:

- **Reactant 1**: Diethyl 2-(3-nitrobenzylidene)malonate — an α,β-unsaturated diester (Michael acceptor) with C:20=C:21 as the activating alkene and C:22=O:23 as one carbonyl.
- **Reactant 2**: 1-(Pyridinium)ketenimine — C:10=C:11=N:12 with pyridinium on C:10.
- **Product**: C:10 adds to C:20 (β-carbon), C:20=C:21 becomes single, C:22=O:23 becomes enolate C:22–O:23⁻, and C:11=N:12 rearranges to C:11≡N:12 (nitrile).

The nucleophilic terminal carbon (C:10) of the ketenimine undergoes 1,4-conjugate addition to the β-position (C:20) of the Michael acceptor, with concomitant enolization and nitrile extrusion from the ketenimine fragment.

**Mechanistic class: Michael addition**

